The paper deals with learning a metric from structured data, which is a common problem in machine learning. The use of dissimilarity matrices and the optimization of metric constraints suggest that the paper belongs to the sub-category of machine learning, cs.LG. The paper also mentions the use of node attributes and edge structure, which are common in graph-based machine learning, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.AI or cs.CV. The mention of computational complexity and optimization techniques suggest that it could also belong to cs.SI or cs.DS.
